solutions.content:
As an optional optimization, we exit early if `res` cannot be improved anymore.


```cpp
int getMinDistance(vector<int>& nums, int target, int start) {
    int res = INT_MAX;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size() && res > abs(start - i); ++i)
        if (nums[i] == target)
            res = abs(start - i);
    return res;
}
```
Another optimization is to initiate the search from the `start` position. It is potentially faster when the `target` is close to the `start`.
```cpp
int getMinDistance(vector<int>& nums, int t, int start) {
    int i = 0, sz = nums.size();
    while (nums[max(0, start - i)] != t && nums[min(start + i, sz - 1)] != t)
        ++i;
    return i;
}
```

