solutions.content:
There are two ways to solve this problem.

1. Doing a sequential traversal of array and updating the min(abs(start-i), min) whenever nums[i] == target.
2. Second is to use two pointers,  have two pointers starting from start and let them move in opposite directions. Whenever we reach the target, this is closest to start.

Code for 2nd approach:

```
int getMinDistance(vector<int>& nums, int target, int start) {
        int i = start, j = start;

        while(i >= 0 or j <= nums.size()-1) {
            if(i >= 0 and nums[i] == target) break;
            if(j <= nums.size() - 1 and nums[j] == target) break;

            j++;
            i--;
        }

        if(i >= 0 and nums[i] == target) {
            return abs(start - i);
        }

        return abs(start - j);
    }
```

