# Intuition
Check every elemet from the right of start, find the shortest distance.

Go back to start, and do the same thing for elements to the left of start.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$: 1 iteration over the array total

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$ Local variables have a single value, regardless of size

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int GetMinDistance(int[] nums, int target, int start) {

        int direction = 1;
        int shortestRight = int.MaxValue;
        int shortestLeft = int.MaxValue;

        for(int i = start; i >= 0; i += direction)
        {
            if(i == nums.Length)
            {
                i = start;
                direction *= -1;
                continue;
            }

            if(nums[i] == target)
            {
                if(direction > 0)
                {
                    shortestRight = Math.Abs(i - start);
                    direction *= -1;
                    i = start;
                } 
                else
                {
                    shortestLeft = Math.Abs(start - i); 
                    break;
                } 
            }
        }

        return Math.Min(shortestRight, shortestLeft);
    }
}
```

