# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We have given the target element and the element from which we have to start. 
We iterate through the array , check where our target value lies and calculate the minimum distance.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Declared two variables max and min which are initially initialised as the Integer.MAX_VALUE;
- Then we iterate through the array,  and whenever we encounter our target element we store it's index to the max variable.
- Now to calculate the minimum distance between the index, we use the Math.min() function where the parameters are the min value itself alongwith the positive difference between the max variable value and the start value.
- We then return the min value.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int getMinDistance(int[] nums, int target, int start) {
        int max = Integer.MAX_VALUE; 
        int min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        for(int i = 0 ; i < nums.length ; i++){
            if(nums[i] == target){
                max = i;

                min = Math.min(min , Math.abs(max - start));
            }
        }   
        return min;
    }
}
```

