# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
My first thought to solve this problem is to use a greedy algorithm. We can keep track of the number of swaps we need to make by looping through the two strings and swapping any characters that are out of order.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
My approach to solving this problem is to use a greedy algorithm. We will loop through both strings and keep track of the number of swaps we need to make. To do this, we will compare the characters of each string and swap any that are out of order. We will continue this loop until all the characters are in the correct order.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n^2)$$
- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

