solutions.content:
We need to find the next permutation, according to [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation), this is how you find it: 
1. Find the largest index k such that a[k] < a[k + 1]. If no such index exists, the permutation is the last permutation.
2. Find the largest index l greater than k such that a[k] < a[l].
3. Swap the value of a[k] with that of a[l].
4. Reverse the sequence from a[k + 1] up to and including the final element a[n].

You can also practice next permutation at https://leetcode.com/problems/next-permutation/. In fact, I recommend that you do that question first before even attempting this question.

The below is my solution: 
```
class Solution {
    public int getMinSwaps(String num, int k) {
        char[] result = num.toCharArray();
        while(--k >= 0){ //next permutation, do it k times
            int swap = result.length - 2; 
            while(swap >= 0 && result[swap] >= result[swap + 1]) --swap;
            int pair = result.length - 1;
            while(pair > swap && result[swap] >= result[pair]) --pair;
            swap(result, swap, pair);
            int lo = swap + 1;
            int hi = result.length - 1;
            while(lo < hi) swap(result, lo++, hi--);
        }


        int ans = 0;
        char[] arr = num.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
            if (arr[i] == result[i]) continue;
            int j = i;
            while(arr[i] != result[j]) ++j; //find the matching character 
            ans += j - i; //number of swap needed to make it match
            while(--j >= i) swap(result, j, j + 1); //match it
        }

        return ans;
    }

    private static void swap(char[] arr, int a, int b){
        char tmp = arr[a];
        arr[a] = arr[b];
        arr[b] = tmp;
    }
}
