solutions.content:
# Intuition
Priority Queue / heap

# Approach
let me explain the line
`PriorityQueue<int[]> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((x,y)->((x[1]-x[0]) - (y[1]-y[0])));`
try to understand other parts of code by yourself.

so, `(x,y)->((x[1]-x[0]) - (y[1]-y[0]))` this line is a lamda expression which will compare difference between distance of two points and it will provide order pair
lets try to understand it using 3 cases.
1. if we add [1,2] then [3,5]
[1,2] will be in heap considering heap was previoulsy empty when we will add [3,5] lambda expression will return (2-1)-(5-3)=-1
which means it is not the smallest and it will not be head of the heap. , `so if it gets any negative result it will add below head.`

2. if we add [2,5] then [3,5]
[2,5] will be in heap considering heap was previoulsy empty when we will add [3,4] lambda expression will return (5-2)-(5-3)=1
which means new pair is going to be the head, `so if it gets any positive result it will make it head.`

3. if we add [1,2] then [3,4]
[1,2] will be in heap considering heap was previoulsy empty when we will add [3,5] lambda expression will return (2-1)-(4-3)=0
which means it is not the smallest and it will not be head of the heap. In this case head will be the pair which was inserted into heap first. `so if it get 0 new pair will added below head of heap.`
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(IlogI + QlogQ)

- Space complexity:
O(I + Q)

// here I is size of interval and Q is size of queries
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] minInterval(int[][] intervals, int[] queries) {
        HashMap<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>(); 
        Arrays.sort(intervals,(x,y)->(x[0]-y[0]));
        int arr[] = new int[queries.length],i=0;
        PriorityQueue<int[]> pq = new PriorityQueue<>((x,y)->((x[1]-x[0]) - (y[1]-y[0])));
        for(int j=0;j<arr.length;j++) arr[j]=queries[j];
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        for(int q : arr){
            while(i<intervals.length && intervals[i][0]<=q){
                pq.offer(intervals[i++]);
            }
            while(pq.size()!=0 && pq.peek()[1]<q){
                pq.poll();
            }
            map.put(q,(pq.size()==0)?-1:pq.peek()[1]-pq.peek()[0]+1);
        }
        for(i=0;i<queries.length;i++){
            queries[i]=map.get(queries[i]);
        }
        return queries;
    }
}
```

