# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For each query, we will have several candidate intervals which contain it and we want to find the one with smallest interval span. So using a priority queue as minheap is reasonable.

However, we cannot tolerate the time complexity $O(nq)$ to finding all the possible candidate intervals for each query every time, so we have to sort both of them to make each interval be inserted into and removed from the minheap at most once.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Sort the query from small to large and sort the intervals from smallest start point to greatest.

Since the query `q_i` is now ever-increasing, so for each time we only have to 
1. add all the residual intervals with starting point `<= q_i` into the priority queue,
2. remove intervals in priority queue with end point `< q_i`, and 
3. finally query the minimal value in the priority queue. 

Since the starting point of the interval is ever increasing, when doing step 1, we can keep a pointer `ptr` pointing to the first interval that is not added in the previous query. As a result, each interval may be put into the minheap at most once and removed at most once.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$O(n\log n + q\log q + n\log n)$: Sort interval + sort query + push each intervals into the minheap at most once 
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$O(q + n)$: n for minheap and q for storing the queries and their indexes.
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> minInterval(vector<vector<int>>& intervals, vector<int>& queries) {
        int q = queries.size();
        vector<pair<int, int>> v;
        vector<int> res (q);
        for (int i = 0;i < q; ++i) {
            v.push_back({queries[i], i});
        }

        ::sort(begin(v), end(v));
        ::sort(begin(intervals), end(intervals));

        int ptr = 0, n = intervals.size();
        priority_queue<pair<int, int>, vector<pair<int,int>>, greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
        for (int i = 0; i < q; ++i) {
            auto [x, idx] = v[i];
            // insert all intervals with a start point  <= x
            while (ptr < n && intervals[ptr][0] <= x) {
                pq.push({intervals[ptr][1] -intervals[ptr][0] + 1, intervals[ptr][1]});
                ++ptr;
            }
            // remove all interval with an end point < x
            while (!pq.empty() && pq.top().second < x) {
                pq.pop();
            }
            res[idx] = pq.empty()?-1:pq.top().first;
        }
        return res;

    }
};
```

