# Intuition
add all the possible intervals for the given query and pick the one which has minimum interval size.

# Approach
sort the queries.(we maintain a datastructure to keep track of indices of each query)
sort the intervals in ascending order
remove element from heap if current query is greater than the "end" interval of the peek.
add all valid intervals to heap.
if heap is empty, then store -1 in result else size of the peek interval

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
  O(nlogn)

- Space complexity:
  O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] minInterval(int[][] intervals, int[] queries) {
        int[][] queriesIdx =new int[queries.length][2];
        for(int i=0;i<queries.length;i++){
            queriesIdx[i]=new int[]{queries[i],i};
        }
        Arrays.sort(queriesIdx,(q1,q2)->(q1[0]-q2[0]));
        Arrays.sort(intervals, (i1,i2)->{
            if(i1[0]==i2[0]) return i1[1]-i2[1];
            return i1[0]-i2[0];
        });
        int[] result = new int[queries.length];
        PriorityQueue<int[]> heap = new PriorityQueue<>((a,b)->{
            return (a[1]-a[0]+1)-(b[1]-b[0]+1);
        });
        int pos=0;
        for(int i=0;i<queries.length;i++){
            while(!heap.isEmpty() && queriesIdx[i][0]>heap.peek()[1]){
                heap.poll();
            }
            while(pos<intervals.length && intervals[pos][0]<=queriesIdx[i][0]){
                  if(queriesIdx[i][0]>=intervals[pos][0] && queriesIdx[i][0]<=intervals[pos][1]){
                      heap.add(new int[]{intervals[pos][0],intervals[pos][1]});
                  }
                  pos++;
            }
            if(heap.isEmpty()) result[queriesIdx[i][1]]=-1;
            else result[queriesIdx[i][1]]=heap.peek()[1]-heap.peek()[0]+1;
        }
        return result;
    }
}
